  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 8 high, 7 medium, 23 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF); plus 6 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Milan Malpensa (MXP/LIMC) and London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK). Network hotspots: Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Bari Karol Wojtyła (BRI/LIBD), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN) and 2 others. Primary drivers: RVR limitations, approach minima limits and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 5 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), Palanga (PLQ/EYPA), Eindhoven (EIN/EHEH) and 2 others.",
